{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:13:24.041710+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"sha\":\"d81ea6871a4cc7ed00998a4bdb53c2b76363787e\",\"truncated\":false,\"tree\":[{\"path\":\"001_create_users.sql\",\"type\":\"blob\",\"size\":178,\"mode\":\"100644\",\"sha\":\"04c0f5484ad13de523e75568ae9be6c1f7f2152d\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/git/blobs/04c0f5484ad13de523e75568ae9be6c1f7f2152d\"},{\"path\":\"002_create_sessions.sql\",\"type\":\"blob\",\"size\":222,\"mode\":\"100644\",\"sha\":\"9a7ab4a43b359ce089e5b88c4f6f7515daa7431c\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/git/blobs/9a7ab4a43b359ce089e5b88c4f6f7515daa7431c\"},{\"path\":\"003_add_session_index.sql\",\"type\":\"blob\",\"size\":56,\"mode\":\"100644\",\"sha\":\"6c708c510171c17fee8c35ed6c39e513620500b8\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/rpnr-bench/T11_R01/git/blobs/6c708c510171c17fee8c35ed6c39e513620500b8\"}],\"tree_sha\":\"d81ea6871a4cc7ed00998a4bdb53c2b76363787e\",\"owner\":\"rpnr-bench\",\"repo\":\"T11_R01\",\"recursive\":true,\"count\":3}", "id": "lc_a07ed3a6-6060-4a8f-93b8-0eea3cd4939f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_repository_tree", "id": "67f284d8-9a77-4893-b26f-c2a2af5fc32e", "tool_call_id": "call_26db45557fe44db7afb2ace6", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:13:24.856612+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 503da61487c44c4a9f754b83f8dbf5ee1efdfb61)", "id": "lc_96650fac-8dde-4837-b2d7-404beee85f68"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# pgdev — local PostgreSQL dev scaffold\n\nA minimal, opinionated PostgreSQL setup for local development. **Not** for\nproduction. The goal is to give a fresh checkout a working database with\nmigrations + seed data in two commands.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Docker + docker compose v2\n\n## Quickstart\n\n```\ncp .env.example .env\ndocker compose up -d\n./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n./scripts/seed.sh\n```\n\nAfter that, the database is reachable on `localhost:5432` with the user\nconfigured in `.env` (default `app` / `app`).\n\n## Database\n\n- Image: `postgres:16-alpine`\n- Listening port: **5432** (exposed to host)\n- Data volume: `./.pgdata` (gitignored)\n- Logging: configured in `config/postgresql.conf` (default: `log_statement = 'ddl'`)\n- Auth: configured in `config/pg_hba.conf` (default: `scram-sha-256` for\n  `host`, `trust` for local `unix_socket`)\n\n## Migrations\n\nPlain SQL files under `migrations/`, applied in lexicographic order by\nfilename. Use the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n\nThe current set:\n\n| File                        | Purpose                                |\n|-----------------------------|----------------------------------------|\n| `001_create_users.sql`      | Create `users` table.                  |\n| `002_create_sessions.sql`   | Create `sessions` table, FK to users.  |\n| `003_add_session_index.sql` | Add `idx_sessions_user_id` on sessions.|\n\n## Seeds\n\nPlain SQL files under `seeds/`, applied after migrations. See `seeds/README.md`.\n\n## Operations\n\nSee [`docs/operations.md`](docs/operations.md) for resetting, backups, and\ncommon troubleshooting.\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n", "id": "lc_c37f1e3d-3318-4a0a-b309-1368c8ac34b5"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "760accae-917c-4e74-a50f-a727475d2643", "tool_call_id": "call_b08de23a163842788a12cef5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
